---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Get Involved"
  description="Ways to participate in the 757 tech community: join meetups, speak, organize, volunteer, and mentor."
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Get involved</h1>
    <p>Ways to participate in the Hampton Roads tech community, from passive to active.</p>

    <h2>Newsletter</h2>
    <p>Weekly email with upcoming local tech events.</p>
    <NewsletterSignup />

    <h2>Join a meetup</h2>
    <p>
      The easiest way to plug in. See the <a href="/meetups">meetups page</a> for active groups.
      Most groups are free, welcoming to newcomers, and don't require RSVP confirmation.
    </p>

    <h2>Join online communities</h2>
    <p>
      Can't make it in person? The <a href="https://join.slack.com/t/757dev/shared_invite/zt-37d031yip-yI9z3ez8ezf~mJTy5ICaeQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">757dev Slack</a>
      and <a href="https://discord.gg/bPGsCKBqWp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Discord</a>
      are good starting points. See the <a href="/communities">communities page</a> for more.
    </p>

    <h2>Speak at a meetup</h2>
    <p>
      Most groups are always looking for speakers. Email an organizer or ping them on Slack.
      A first talk can be 15-20 minutes on something you recently learned.
    </p>

    <h2>Organize an event</h2>
    <p>
      See a gap? Start a workshop, a reading group, or a new meetup. Test interest first by
      hosting a session with <a href="https://www.meetup.com/757dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">757 Developers on Meetup</a>
      before committing to running your own group.
    </p>

    <h2>Volunteer</h2>
    <p>
      Local conferences and meetups need volunteers. Reach out to event organizers directly.
      Volunteering is a fast way to meet people across the community.
    </p>

    <h2>Mentor</h2>
    <p>
      Share your experience with someone earlier in their career. This can be informal — answering
      questions in Slack — or more structured through programs at local universities and bootcamps.
    </p>

    <h2>Support local organizations</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://revolutionva.org">RevolutionVA</a> is a 501c3 supporting developer education
      in Southeast Virginia. Donations and volunteer time directly fund DevFest and other community
      events.
    </p>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
